'''Samed Baždar''' ({{IPA|sr|sǎmed bǎʒdar|pron}}; born 31 January 2004) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Ekstraklasa]] club [[Jagiellonia Białystok]], on loan from Spanish club [[Real Zaragoza|Zaragoza]]. Born in Serbia, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Baždar started his professional career at [[FK Partizan|Partizan]], before joining Zaragoza in 2024, who loaned him to Jagiellonia in 2026.

A former Serbian youth international, Baždar also made his senior international debut for [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]], before switching his allegiance to Bosnia and Herzegovina in 2024, earning 13 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Partizan===
Baždar started playing football at local clubs, before joining [[FK Partizan Academy|Partizan's youth academy]] in 2018. In December 2020, he signed his first professional contract with the team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportal.blic.rs/fudbal/domaci-fudbal/moze-kao-poluspic-a-moze-i-kao-centarfor-partizan-vezao-najtalentovanijeg-fudbalera-svoje-generacije/2022042018402226308|title=Može kao polušpic, a može i kao centarfor: Partizan "vezao" najtalentovanijeg fudbalera svoje generacije|website=blic.rs|date=16 December 2020|accessdate=16 December 2020|language=Serbian}}</ref> He made his professional debut against [[FK Voždovac|Voždovac]] on 15 May 2021 at the age of 17.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://telegraf.rs/sport/fudbal/3339378-partizan-prosao-prvu-generalku-pred-finale-kupa-crno-beli-sa-tri-komada-resili-zabrinuti-vozdovac|title=Partizan prošao prvu generalku pred finale Kupa: Crno-beli sa tri komada rešili zabrinuti Voždovac|website=telegraf.rs|date=15 May 2021|accessdate=16 May 2021|language=Serbian}}</ref> On 9 July 2022, he scored his first professional goal in a triumph over [[FK Javor Ivanjica|Javor]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mozzartsport.com/fudbal/vesti/pricalo-se-da-nema-bonuse-a-onda-je-stolica-lansirao-dvojicu-petkovic-i-bazdar-za-sjaj-partizana-u-ivanjici/424804|title=Pričalo se da nema bonuse, a onda je Stolica lansirao dvojicu: Petković i Baždar za sjaj Partizana u Ivanjici|website=mozzartsport.com|date=9 July 2022|accessdate=11 July 2022|language=Serbian}}</ref>

In August, he signed a new four-year deal with the squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kurir.rs/sport/fudbal/3988245/partizanov-biser-produzio-ugovor-na-jos-dve-godine-bazdar-za-bolju-buducnost-crno-belih|title=Partizanov biser produžio ugovor na još dve godine: Baždar za bolju budućnost crno-belih|website=kurir.rs|date=10 August 2022|accessdate=11 August 2022|language=Serbian}}</ref>

===Zaragoza===
In July 2024, Baždar was transferred to Spanish side [[Real Zaragoza|Zaragoza]] for an undisclosed transfer fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://telegraf.rs/sport/fudbal/3930213-bazdaru-drhtao-glas-na-oprostaju-od-partizana-ako-bog-da-slavicemo-titulu-narednog-leta|title=Baždaru drhtao glas na oproštaju od Partizana: Ako Bog da, slavićemo titulu narednog leta|website=telegraf.rs|date=17 July 2024|accessdate=19 July 2024|language=Serbian}}</ref> He made his official debut for the club on 16 August against [[Cádiz CF|Cádiz]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mozzartsport.com/fudbal/vesti/bazdar-debitovao-za-saragosu-prva-asistencija-pala-za-14-minuta/489751|title=Baždar debitovao za Saragosu: Prva asistencija pala za 14 minuta|website=mozzartsport.com|date=16 August 2024|accessdate=16 August 2024|language=Serbian}}</ref> On 21 September, he scored his first goal for Real Zaragoza against [[Levante UD|Levante]], which secured the victory for his team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mozzartsport.com/fudbal/vesti/bazdar-se-predstavio-romaredi-majstorija-za-preokret-i-saragosin-skok-na-vrh/492371|title=Baždar se predstavio Romaredi: Majstorija za preokret i Saragosin skok na vrh|website=mozzartsport.ba|date=21 September 2024|accessdate=21 September 2024|language=Serbian}}</ref>

In January 2026, he was loaned to Polish outfit [[Jagiellonia Białystok]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/ino-fudbal/samed-bazdar-zvanicno-napustio-spaniju-predstavljen-je-kao-veliko-pojacanje-u-novom-klubu-1108414|title=Samed Baždar zvanično napustio Španiju: Predstavljen je kao veliko pojačanje u novom klubu|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=25 January 2026|accessdate=26 January 2026|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

==International career==
After representing [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] at all youth levels, Baždar made his senior international debut in a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] game against [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]] on 25 March 2024. However, in October, he decided that he would play for [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] in the future.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/reprezentativac-srbije-potvrdio-da-ce-igrati-za-bosnu-i-hercegovinu-odluka-je-cisto-sportska/566430|title=Reprezentativac Srbije potvrdio da će igrati za Bosnu i Hercegovinu: Odluka je čisto sportska|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=1 November 2024|accessdate=1 November 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

In November, his request to change sports citizenship from Serbian to Bosnian was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/939356/sretno-novom-zmaju-samed-bazdar-je-od-danas-zvanicno-drzavljanin-bih|title=Sretno novom Zmaju: Samed Baždar je od danas zvanično državljanin BiH|website=avaz.ba|date=12 November 2024|accessdate=14 August 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref> Earlier that month, he received his first senior call up, for [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A#Group 3|2024–25 UEFA Nations League A]] matches against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/barbarez-objavio-spisak-za-njemacku-i-nizozemsku-pozvani-bazdar-i-kulenovic/241105053|title=Barbarez objavio spisak za Njemačku i Nizozemsku, pozvani Baždar i Kulenović|website=klix.ba|date=5 November 2024|accessdate=5 November 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 16 November.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/bosna-i-hercegovina-u-njemackoj-primila-sedam-golova/3370246|title=Bosna i Hercegovina u Njemačkoj primila sedam golova|website=fokus.ba|date=16 November 2024|accessdate=19 November 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

On 6 September 2025, in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group H|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] against [[San Marino national football team|San Marino]], Baždar scored his first senior international goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/481613-zmajevi-razbili-san-marino-u-gostima|title=Zmajevi razbili San Marino u gostima|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=6 September 2025|accessdate=9 September 2025|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

In May 2026, Baždar was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/reprezentacija/barbarez-objavio-spisak-ovih-26-igraca-ide-na-svjetsko-prvenstvo/3546757|title=Barbarez objavio spisak: Ovih 26 igrača ide na Svjetsko prvenstvo|website=fokus.ba|date=11 May 2026|access-date=11 May 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

